<h1 class="govuk-u-bold-48 govuk-u-mb-6 app-u-mb-4--small">Register for Self Assessment</h1>

<% page_content = capture do %>


<p>You need to register for Self Assessment before you file your tax return.</p>

<p>There are different ways to register if you’re:</p>

<ul>
  <li><a href="/log-in-file-self-assessment-tax-return/register-if-youre-self-employed">self-employed or a sole trader</a></li>
  <li><a href="/log-in-file-self-assessment-tax-return/register-if-youre-not-self-employed">not self-employed</a></li>
  <li><a href="/log-in-file-self-assessment-tax-return/register-if-youre-a-partner-or-partnership">registering a partner or partnership</a></li>
</ul>

<div role="note" aria-label="Information" class="application-notice info-notice">
<p>Allow enough time to complete the registration process so you can send your return by the <a href="/self-assessment-tax-returns/deadlines">deadline</a>.</p>
</div>

<h2 id="if-you-have-already-registered">If you have already registered</h2>

<p>Once you’re registered, you have to activate your Government Gateway account using your Unique Taxpayer Reference (UTR).</p>

<p>You can <a rel="external" href="https://www.tax.service.gov.uk/government-gateway-registration-frontend/choose-your-account?continue=%2Faccount&amp;origin=unknown">create a Government Gateway account</a> if you don’t have one.</p>

<div role="note" aria-label="Information" class="application-notice info-notice">
<p>Don’t create a new account if you’ve activated one before. You can only link your UTR to one Government Gateway account.</p>
</div>

<% end %>

